            <title>[GROOVY-1912] GroovyScriptEngine.loadScriptByName is the cause of Stack Overflow Error</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-1912</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;ClassLoader cl = getClass().getClassLoader();&lt;br/&gt;
def engine = new GroovyScriptEngine(&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;&amp;quot;file://.&amp;quot;&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;*.toURL() as URL[], cl);&lt;br/&gt;
engine.loadScriptByName(&quot;TestGroovy2&quot;).newInstance();	  &lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Exception in thread &quot;main&quot; java.lang.StackOverflowError&lt;br/&gt;
	at groovy.util.GroovyScriptEngine.loadScriptByName(GroovyScriptEngine.java:283)&lt;br/&gt;
	at groovy.util.GroovyScriptEngine.loadScriptByName(GroovyScriptEngine.java:283)&lt;br/&gt;
	at groovy.util.GroovyScriptEngine.loadScriptByName(GroovyScriptEngine.java:283)&lt;br/&gt;
.......&lt;/p&gt;</description>
